Description: 
Like I'm a Celebrity... but without the jungly deprivations, 
this sends five so-called celebrities to a South African 
villa, where they vie to be the perfect holiday companion. 
For Stuart "the brand" Baggs of The Apprentice, that 
means sniping at Christopher Biggins about his treatment 
of the staff, and for high-maintenance model Paula 
Hamilton it means strops about confined spaces and 
sugary food. Five minutes in, you'll know you'd never 
want to go on holiday with her. For "fun", each organises 
an activity (ranging from a heritage tour to a zip-line 
challenge) that they hope will get the others' votes. 
Shamefully compulsive viewing.
